{"action": "input", "code": "def find_red_and_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    red_pixels = np.where(input_grid == red)\n    teal_pixels = np.where(input_grid == teal)\n    return (red_pixels, teal_pixels)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    r, t = find_red_and_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    r_c, t_c = check_pixels(r, t)\n    out = color_teal_pixels(r, t, r_c, t_c, input_grid)\n    return out\ndef color_teal_pixels(r: Tuple[np.ndarray], t: Tuple[np.ndarray], r_c: int, t_c: int, input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Colors the teal pixels in the input grid according to the condition of pixels in teal.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    r (Tuple[np.ndarray]): Tuple containing the row indices of red pixels in the input grid.\n    t (Tuple[np.ndarray]): Tuple containing the row indices of teal pixels in the input grid.\n    r_c (int): Condition of pixels in red.\n    t_c (int): Condition of pixels in teal.\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): Input grid containing the pixels to be colored.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: Grid with colored teal pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    out = input_grid.copy()\n    for i in range(len(t[0])):\n        row, col = (t[0][i], t[1][i])\n        if t_c == 1:\n            while row not in r[0]:\n                out[row][col] = teal\n                row += 1\n                if row == input_grid.shape[0]:\n                    break\n        else:\n            while col not in r[1]:\n                out[row][col] = teal\n                col += 1\n                if col == input_grid.shape[1]:\n                    break\n    return out\ndef check_pixels(r: Tuple[np.ndarray], t: Tuple[np.ndarray]) -> int:\n    if len(set(r[0])) == 1 and len(set(t[0])) == 1:\n        return 1\n    elif len(set(r[1])) == 1 and len(set(t[1])) == 1:\n        return 2\n    else:\n        return 0", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    r, t = `find the red pixels and teal pixel